Malawi Central Bank Considers Islamic Bank Proposal, Times Says

-- B y   F r a n k   J o m o
-- 
2011-02-17T12:43:34Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-17/malawi-central-bank-considers-islamic-bank-proposal-times-says.html
     Feb.17 (Bloomberg) ---Shariah Investment Ltd. is in talks
with Malawi’s central bank to open a bank that will follow the
principles of Islamic finance, the Daily Times reported, citing
Shariah Investment’s Chairman Iqbar Omar.  The country has a population of about 15.5 million of which
13 percent are Muslim, according to the CIA Factbook.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Frank Jomo in Blantyre at 
 fjomo@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net  